</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C366657DFFA44405D3EBFF2EFBE0FE0D" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA44405D3EBFF2EFBE0FE0D" blockId="6.[151,1437,223,394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">
The type of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA44405D263FF11FDD4FF7D" authority="(Luzon)" baseAuthorityName="Luzon" box="[287,520,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA44405D263FF11FE7AFF7D" box="[287,422,224,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">N. marcipor</emphasis>
(Luzon)
</taxonomicName>
is a taxon with a very short lateral tubercle (about as long as wide), not dissimilar from that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA44405D25CFEF5FE60FE99" baseAuthorityName="J. Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[288,444,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA44405D25CFEF5FE60FE99" box="[288,444,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">N. conspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens from Panay and Mindanao show tubercles two or three times as long as wide; nonetheless, the 
<typeStatus id="54C78854FFA44405D225FED6FE67FEC5" box="[345,443,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA44405D294FED6FCEDFEC5" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1980" box="[488,817,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Mimanhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaonis">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA44405D294FED6FCEDFEC5" box="[488,817,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Mimanhammus mindanaonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
perfectly corresponds to the population from Luzon. Whether this type was destroyed and later substituted or two different forms inhabit these southern islands could be clarified by the 
<typeStatus id="54C78854FFA44405D234FE81FE74FE0E" box="[328,424,368,394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">paratype</typeStatus>
preserved in 
<collectingRegion id="49B8F814FFA44405D13CFE9EFD56FE0D" box="[576,650,367,393]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="6" pageNumber="85">Berlin</collectingRegion>
. Currently, it is not available for study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
